
Versatile approach to the synthesis of tetraarylphosphonium salts bearing 3,4-dihydroxynaphthyl substituent




 
Â© 2015 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved. Diphenylphosphine easily reacts with two molecules of 1,2-naphthoquinone or 6-bromo-1,2-naphthoquinone to give zwitterions, the products of addition at the C-4 position of the quinone, which were converted into the corresponding tetraarylphosphonium salts by treatment with mineral acid.


